        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 6 at 6:48PM MDT until June 6 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 648 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 14 miles southwest
of Clayton, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Clayton.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT Friday for a
portion of northeast New Mexico.</instruction>
